  "summary": "Malicious code in autotel-mcp (npm)",
  "details": "This version is part of a supply-chain compromise of the autotel publisher pipeline. The package ships a ~4.5MB index.js containing a ROT13/ROT-cipher eval decoder that injects and executes a hidden payload on module import (require-time), with no install hook needed — code injection runs on every import. The affected releases were later deprecated with the note \"SECURITY: compromised supply-chain build.\"",
